A short-term solution in the case of {{open_dataset()}} and CSVs without headers would be to instead specify the column names as such: 

{code:r}
random_without_headers <- open_dataset(
  'random_without_header.csv',
  schema = random_schema,
  format = 'csv',
  read_options = CsvReadOptions$create(column_names = names(random_schema))
)
{code}

However, this isn't great - I'll see if I can get this happening automatically.

